  "articleSummary": "The article \"Visualizing Promises\" uses animated timelines to clarify how JavaScript Promises execute, emphasizing timing and common pitfalls. It critiques a frequent mistake—invoking `console.log` directly in `.then()` without wrapping it in a function—which causes immediate execution instead of deferred resolution. Through four examples, it demonstrates sequential and parallel Promise behavior, including `Promise.all` for concurrent resolution tracking. The tone is tutorial-focused, with a pragmatic approach to debugging asynchronous code. Key technologies discussed include `setTimeout`, `.then()`, and `Promise.all`, framed through visual metaphors of timelines to reinforce execution order and timing.",
